index.html.title: ATON 3.0 API
index.html.name: ATON 3.0 API
index.html.summary: ATON is a framework to create Web3D apps (presenters, applied games, tools, etc…) interacting with CH objects and 3D scenes on the Web. It adopts a 'develop once, deploy everywhere' approach, without requiring any installation for final users, with its front-end automatically adapting to the device (mobile, desktop/kiosk or immersive VR).

LightProbe.html.title: LightProbe
LightProbe.html.name: LightProbe
LightProbe.html.description: Class representing a light probe (LP), can be static or updated at runtime

LightProbe.html#update.title: update()
LightProbe.html#update.name: update
LightProbe.html#update.description: Update LP capture. Typically called when all 3D models are loaded and arranged into the scene. Can be called at runtime or whenever there is some change in the 3D scene

POV.html.title: POV
POV.html.name: POV
POV.html.description: Class representing a Viewpoint (POV) in the 3D space, abstracting from device used (mobile, desktop or immersive XR). Constructor allows to assign the POV a unique ID (string)

POV.html#setFOV.title: setFOV( f )
POV.html#setFOV.name: setFOV
POV.html#setFOV.description: Set field of view (FOV) in degrees

POV.html#hasKeyword.title: hasKeyword( kw ) → {boolean}
POV.html#hasKeyword.name: hasKeyword
POV.html#hasKeyword.description: Returns true if this viewpoint has specific keyword

Node.html.title: Node
Node.html.name: Node
Node.html.description: Class representing an ATON node. Constructor allows to create different types (scene nodes, semantic nodes and UI nodes)

Node.html#addKeywords.title: addKeywords( kw )
Node.html#addKeywords.name: addKeywords
Node.html#addKeywords.description: Add keyword(s) to this node. Keywords are also recursively added into the sub-graph

Node.html#hasKeyword.title: hasKeyword( kw ) → {boolean}

Node.html#hasKeyword.description: Returns true if this node has specific keyword

Node.html#hide.title: hide()
Node.html#hide.name: hide
Node.html#hide.description: Hide this node (and sub-graph), also invisible to queries (ray casting, picking)

Node.html#show.title: show()
Node.html#show.name: show
Node.html#show.description: Show this node (and sub-graph). If pickable, becomes sensible to queries (ray casting)

Node.html#toggle.title: toggle()
Node.html#toggle.name: toggle
Node.html#toggle.description: Toggle node visibility. If visible, becomes invisible, and viceversa.

Node.html#disablePicking.title: disablePicking()
Node.html#disablePicking.name: disablePicking
Node.html#disablePicking.description: Disable this node for runtime queries (ray casters). Useful for instance on vegetation, etc...

Node.html#enablePicking.title: enablePicking()
Node.html#enablePicking.name: enablePicking
Node.html#enablePicking.description: Enable this node for runtime queries (ray casters)

Node.html#setMaterial.title: setMaterial( M )
Node.html#setMaterial.name: setMaterial
Node.html#setMaterial.description: Set cascading material. Note this applies to this node and all children (even all those still loading)

Node.html#removeChildren.title: removeChildren()
Node.html#removeChildren.name: removeChildren
Node.html#removeChildren.description: Delete all children of this node

Node.html#attachTo.title: attachTo( node )
Node.html#attachTo.name: attachTo

Node.html#attachToRoot.title: attachToRoot()
Node.html#attachToRoot.name: attachToRoot
Node.html#attachToRoot.description: Attach this node to main root. This is usually mandatory in order to visualize the node and all its descendants. Depending on node type this will be the scene root (visible scene-graph), the semantic-graph root or UI root

Node.html#getBound.title: getBound() → {THREE.Sphere}

Node.html#load.title: load( url, onComplete )

Node.html#load.description: Load a 3D model under this node, with optional onComplete handler. Note the system will take care of loading the resources in background, and will manage duplicate requests to same resources avoiding waste of bandwidth
